SPECIAL MEETING ANNOUNCEMENT: The Jefferson Township Board of Education will hold a SPECIAL MEETING on Monday, August 24, 2020 at 7:00pm. The purpose of this special meeting is to discuss personnel-related matters. Action may be taken. The Board may convene to Executive Session immediately following public session.

The meeting will be conducted via video and/or teleconference and will be open to the public. A link to register for the meeting will be posted on the district website on the day of the meeting.

post_text:
Please be advised that on Friday, June 5, all students in Jefferson Township Schools will participate in a technology-free, no screen-time learning day. This special learning day will begin after students have checked their teachers’ Google Classroom for individual assignments. As such, students will be responsible for assignments on June 5th; however, the assigned work will be provided in a manner that does not require the use of a computer or other related technology sources. Please note that some teachers may ask students to use their phone/device to take pictures or video. More detailed information will be posted within teachers’ Google Classrooms.

We hope this unique learning day provides students a restful break from the engaged computer technology learning experience.

Thank you for your attention to this matter.

post_text: At the May 18th BOE meeting, this year's school calendar was revised to reflect changes in unused snow days. Virtual learning allows the district to change the last day of school. Schools will no longer be closed on May 21 and May 22 as outlined in the original calendar, the district will now be closed on June 12, June 22, and June 23. The last day for students is now Friday, June 19.

post_text:
5/4/2020: Governor Murphy announced today that schools will be closed through the end of the school year. Although our district has started to work on plans in the event of this closure, there will be many things to consider how to virtually end the school year keeping social distancing protocols in mind. We will reach out to the school community as plans formalize. We appreciate your patience as we navigate through this unprecedented and difficult time.

Stay safe and be well.

Jeanne Howe

post_text: If your family has a change in household circumstances, you may be eligible for free and reduced meals for your students. Applications can be found on the district website: https://www.jefftwp.org/Page/1672. Paper applications are available for pick up between 11-12:30 at the Board Office. Applications should be dropped off at that time as well. You may also email completed applications to TShatzel@Jefftwp.org. Please make sure to include all household members as well as the last four digits of your social security number and the signature of the adult household member completing the application.

Dear Parents/Guardians:

At this time, we are asking that all parents and guardians check their access to the Realtime Parent Portal. Please make sure your contact list is updated in order to receive up to date information. Instructions for updating are below.

Contact Tab:
Under the Contact Tab, you can review and edit the contact information that has been provided to the school district. Please check your contacts and make any changes/updates as necessary. Please make sure to include a phone number for the “SMS Text” to receive text message alerts. You will also need to add an email address to receive email alerts.

If you require further assistance, please contact your student’s school.

post_text: We are pleased to report that the boiler at Milton is working. All Pre-School and Kindergarten classes will resume at Milton School tomorrow, Tuesday, January 8th. Thank you for your understanding.
text: We are pleased to report that the boiler at Milton is working. All Pre-School and Kindergarten classes will resume at Milton School tomorrow, Tuesday, January 8th. Thank you for your understanding.

post_text:
Good Morning, Milton Parents:

At this time, the boiler system at Milton School is not working. With the combination of the cold weather this morning and no heat, it will not be possible for our students and staff to remain at Milton School for today.

All students currently at Milton will be transported via district transportation to Cozy Lake School early this morning. Students attending p.m. Pre-School will be dropped off at Cozy Lake School. Any parent drop-offs or pick-ups should be done at Cozy Lake School.

It is our hope that the boiler will be fixed during the day today; we will update you on the progress later today.

post_text:
A false rumor is circulating around social media that our schools are closed tomorrow, November 27th, due to a bomb threat. It is important to note that at no time has there been a bomb threat to any of our schools. Our High School administration took this case of making a false alarm very seriously and immediately started an investigation into the origin of the post. The comment was started by one of our students, meant as a joke. The Jefferson Township Police Department was also notified of the false rumor.

All JTPS schools will be open tomorrow, November 27th, as regularly scheduled.
